According to Dr. Gaylord Lopez, the director of the Georgia Anti-poison Centre, cases of ingestion of hand detergent in children under 12 years of age reported at anti-poison centres went from 3.266 in 2010 to 16.117 in 2014.
"Children have more frequent access to these products and, unfortunately, a percentage of them reach the emergency room," Lopez told CNN.
