Rare illness a man suffers from
The American Nick Hess was suspected by his family of being an alcoholic, his wife even filming him when he was dizzy, he could barely stand up and his words were hard to understand.
Although the 35-year-old man said he didn't drink alcohol, it was obvious that he was intoxicated.
When she first accused me of being drunk without drinking, I thought she was crazy.
"But friends and family thought 'maybe he was drinking alone, he's a secret alcoholic'," he says, according to Mirror.
When he saw his wife's videos of him, the man in Columbus, Ohio, he just didn't recognize himself: "I was looking into my eyes and I wasn't there."
'It was awful, I didn't remember anything.'
Besides, his wife, who, although doubting him for a while, finally went with him to countless doctors, remembers that Nick's breath smelled like alcohol.
The moment that put Nick on his mind the most was when, after a minor accident, when he was hit by another car, it was discovered that he had a three-fold alcohol level over the legal limb, although the night before he had only had one beer.
After years and innumerable investigations, it was discovered that Nick suffers from an extremely rare disease, "Auto-brewery syndrome".
Basically, his body makes all the carbohydrates consumed ferment, turning into alcohol.
The one who suspected this could be Nick's illness was even his wife.
The disease doesn't have a cure yet, but since he quit his carbs, Nick hasn't had such episodes.
